<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1162] Add mechanism to assert/compare SQLStates</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1162</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JUnit test environment needs a mechanism to assert/compare SQLStates. The goal is to be able to reference states from SQLState without having to care if the length of the identifier is 5,7 or more characters long.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A way to do this already exist in StandardException.getSQLStateFromIdentifier, but it is too unwieldy and long. I suggest adding  &apos;assertSQLState(String, String, SQLException)&apos; method to BaseJDBCTestCase.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>JUnit test environment</environment>
